#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. Rule"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 12. Kinnusīhasutta → sīhasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3) | sīho (pts1)
msgctxt "sn4.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Kinnusīhasutta"
msgstr "12. Lion"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.12:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn4.12:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā mahatiyā parisāya parivuto dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr ""
"Now, at that time the Buddha was teaching Dhamma, surrounded by a large "
"assembly."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.110"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.245"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.12:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho mārassa pāpimato etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Māra thought:"

msgctxt "sn4.12:2.2"
msgid "“ayaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo mahatiyā parisāya parivuto dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr "“The ascetic Gotama is teaching Dhamma, surrounded by a large assembly."

# This phrase is more idiomatic than I prefer, but here it captues both the literal sense and the meaning better than any more formal phrase.
msgctxt "sn4.12:2.3"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkameyyaṃ vicakkhukammāyā”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I go and pull the wool over their eyes?”"

msgctxt "sn4.12:2.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.12:3.1"
msgid "“Kinnu sīhova nadasi,"
msgstr "“Why now do you roar like a lion?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.12:3.2"
msgid "parisāyaṃ visārado;"
msgstr "You’re so self-assured in the assembly!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.12:3.3"
msgid "Paṭimallo hi te atthi,"
msgstr "For there is someone who’ll wrestle with you,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.12:3.4"
msgid "vijitāvī nu maññasī”ti."
msgstr "so why do you imagine you’re the victor?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.12:4.1"
msgid "“Nadanti ve mahāvīrā,"
msgstr "“The great heroes they roar,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.12:4.2"
msgid "parisāsu visāradā;"
msgstr "self-assured in the assembly."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.12:4.3"
msgid "Tathāgatā balappattā,"
msgstr "The Realized One, attained to power,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.12:4.4"
msgid "tiṇṇā loke visattikan”ti."
msgstr "has crossed over clinging to the world.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.12:5.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṃ bhagavā, jānāti maṃ sugato”ti dukkhī "
"dummano tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The Buddha knows me! The Holy One knows me!”"
" miserable and sad, vanished right there."
